A fascinating and revealing documentary
tracing the creation and subsequent success
of internationally adored rock band The
Who's rock opera TOMMY titled THE
WHO'S SENSATION: THE STORY OF TOMMY

Furthermore, the official synopsis of THE
WHO'S SENSATION: THE STORY OF TOMMY
is as follows: &quot;1968 was a time of soul searching
for the band - with three badly performing
singles behind them they needed a big new idea
to put them back at the top and crucially to hold
them together as a band. Inspired by Indian
spiritual master Meher Baba, Pete Townshend
created the character of Tommy, the 'deaf,
dumb and blind boy'. Broke and fragmenting
when they started recording, the album went
on to sell over 20 million copies. In this film,
the Who speak for the first time about the
making of the iconic album and how its
success changed their lives.&quot;


